svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bwz1665702567697.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bwz1665702567697.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bwz1665702567697.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bwz1665702567697\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface XML Constructs\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bwz1665702567697__uniface_xml_constructs_530626\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface enables you to use and manipulate data in a variety of ways, including Structs, Uniface XML streams, and component-based APIs, UXMLREADER and UXMLWRITER .\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bwz1665702567697__p_d177614e1_d177615e1_d177616e1\">The following topics describe the common XML constructs and how they may be handled in Uniface.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bwz1665702567697__ul_ak3_yxh_ddc\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zqo1665702698931.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zqo1665702698931.html\" title=\"An XML document may have a an XML declaration on the first line.\">XML Declaration</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gzt1719681576072.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gzt1719681576072.html\" title=\"The DOCTYPE, or Document Type Declaration can contain a reference to a DTD document, and it may contain locally defined declarations.\">XML DOCTYPE Declaration</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jti1665702698857.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jti1665702698857.html\" title=\"A namespace declaration is an attribute with a fixed name xmlns, and which can occur multiple times in one start tag.\">XML Namespace Declaration</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"miy1719664397033.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/miy1719664397033.html\" title=\"An XML element contains a start tag, content, and end tag.\">XML Element</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hmp1665703544187.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hmp1665703544187.html\" title=\"An XML attribute is an identifier associated with an XML tag. It has a unique name in the context of the tag, and a string value. A tag can have any number of attributes, including none.\">XML Attribute</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eqi1665703544277.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eqi1665703544277.html\" title=\"XML comments are embedded within &lt;!-- --&gt; tags.\">XML Comment</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dlu1719819422429.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dlu1719819422429.html\" title=\"Processing instructions embed an application name and an instruction within &lt;? ?&gt; tags.\">XML Processing Instruction</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ajx1665702699086.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Structs for XML Data</a><p>You can use the ProcScript instructions xmlToStruct and structToXml to convert complex data from and to XML.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gpq1665702699272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>XML Streams</a><p>XML streams are data streams using an XML format. They enable loosely coupled connections between components, and provide a standardized format for data transport between components. Uniface can transfer field data and data relationships via XML stream parameters. It can also attach processing information to data in an XML stream to allow the data state to be transported with the data.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tql1665702758597.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>APIs for XML Handling</a><p>You can implement your own XML handlers using the APIs provided by the UXMLREADER and UXMLWRITER components, and SAX callback operations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526280\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526280\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface XML Constructs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface XML Constructs Uniface enables you to use and manipulate data in a variety of ways, including Structs, Uniface XML streams, and component-based APIs, UXMLREADER and UXMLWRITER . The following topics describe the common XML constructs and how they may be handled in Uniface. XML Declaration XML DOCTYPE Declaration XML Namespace Declaration XML Element XML Attribute XML Comment XML Processing Instruction Related Links Structs for XML Data You can use the ProcScript instructions xmlToStruct and structToXml to convert complex data from and to XML. XML Streams XML streams are data streams using an XML format. They enable loosely coupled connections between components, and provide a standardized format for data transport between components. Uniface can transfer field data and data relationships via XML stream parameters. It can also attach processing information to data in an XML stream to allow the data state to be transported with the data. APIs for XML Handling You can implement your own XML handlers using the APIs provided by the UXMLREADER and UXMLWRITER components, and SAX callback operations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}